						               													<description>The game has 72 letter cards and a 1-minute sand timer. With 4 or more players, teams of 2-3 players are recommended.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player (or team) is dealt 8 cards, and each player makes a word of 3 or more letters from their hand. (They may discard and draw 3 cards until they are able to make a word.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In their turn, a player is the Word Hider, who lays out their word face down, turns the first letter face up, and starts the timer.  Each other player shouts out guesses for the word. At any time before the timer runs out, if 2 or more players agree to see another letter, the Word Hider reveals another letter, and the guessing continues.  Once a player correctly guesses the word, the Word Hider says &amp;quot;That's it&amp;quot; and reveals the word; the player who guessed it keeps all the cards that were hidden when the correct guess was made. If no correct guess is made, the Word Hider keeps all the letters of the word.  Unclaimed cards are discarded, and Word Hider fills their hand back to 8 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players keep taking turns being the Word Hider until the deck runs out and no one can make a word from their hand. At that point, the player with the most cards won from guesses is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
